        " الْكَلَالَةُ مَا لَمْ يَكُنْ وَلَدٌ وَ لَا وَالِدٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Faal Bin Shaaan, altogether from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdul Rahman Bin Al Hajjaj, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The ‘<span class=\"iTxt\">Kalala</span>’ is one who is neither a son nor a father’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father and Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan all from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘Abd al-Rahman ibn al-Hajjaj who has narrated the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Kalalah (burdensome people) is one who is not a son or a father.’” "
        ]
      }
